The Renaissance: A Period of Cultural Rebirth

The Renaissance, meaning "rebirth" in French, was a period of European history that spanned from the 14th to the 17th century. This era marked a profound cultural awakening that began in Italy and spread throughout Europe.

Key aspects of the Renaissance include:

  • Revival of classical learning and wisdom
  • Development of humanism
  • Artistic innovations by masters like Leonardo da Vinci and Michelangelo
  • Scientific discoveries and technological advancements
  • Exploration of new lands and trade routes

The Renaissance laid the foundation for modern Western culture and continues to influence our world today through its emphasis on human potential, scientific inquiry, and artistic expression.
